    {
      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<p><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">We are pleased to announce that Source Code sharing is renewed! Please find listed below the changes you can expect:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">Customers will no longer need to request the source code of hotfixes and updates since it will be delivered at the same time when the hotfixes and DXP updates are built. They will be available for download.</span></li>\n<li>\n<span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">Old fix pack/hotfix tags will be renamed to </span><strong><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">legacy-*</span></strong><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\"> </span><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">to avoid confusion. If one downloads a new hotfix (i.e.: 7.4), it will contain both new and old tags. However, we recommend to use the new tag, as legacy tags (</span><strong><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">legacy-*</span></strong><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">) will be deleted by January 2024 with no further notice. </span>\n</li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">Build files will be included in the repository, helping the IDEs to understand the source code structure. Please keep in mind that customers will still not be allowed to build DXP for themselves.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">Customers won’t need to request the source code generation for newer versions (7.4 and 7.3). We will also be making this change to older DXP versions in the near future.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">A hotfix will now become a single commit and not multiple merge commits as they previously were. This change is to ensure that the system can work reliably and the repository size can be smaller.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">We will continue to use the same repository and keep it available as usual.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\">Please note:</span></em></strong><span style=\"color: #6f6f6f;\"> It will take a few days to update all fixes but they will be completed no later than September 15th. If you do not find the source code along with your update, please follow the current process.</span></p>"
      },
